OL,3,CWhat is endometriosis - and why waits
OL,4,Cfor a diagnosis might be speeding up
OL,6,FEvery month, the cells behave the same
OL,7,Fway as those in the womb lining,
OL,8,Fbuilding up before breaking down and
OL,9,Fbleeding.
OL,11,FUnlike what happens to the uterus
OL,12,Fduring a period, blood is isn't able
OL,13,Fto leave the body - causing pain,
OL,14,Finflammation and scarring.
OL,16,FSpeaking on endometriosis, the Women's
OL,17,FHealth Minister Baroness Merron said:
OL,18,F"Endometriosis can be debilitating and
OL,19,Fwomen with this condition have been
OL,20,Ffailed for far too long.
